Instead, the transaction should be rolled back by the application before retrying 'SaveChanges'. See https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2149338 for more information.     SELECT [a].[Id], [a].[Name], [a].[ProvinceId]

If 'SaveChanges' fails, then the transaction cannot be automatically rolled back to a known clean state. Instead, the transaction should be rolled back by the application before retrying 'SaveChanges'. See https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2149338 for more information. To identify the code which triggers this warning, call 'ConfigureWarnings(w => w.Throw(RelationalEventId.SavepointsDisabledBecauseOfMARS))'.

SELECT [Id]
FROM [AbpAuditLogs]
WHERE @@ROWCOUNT = 1 AND [Id] = scope_identity();

SELECT [t].[Id], [t].[Name], [t].[ProvinceId], [a1].[Id], [a1].[Name], (
    SELECT COUNT(*)
    FROM [AbpTenants] AS [a]
    WHERE ((@__ef_filter__p_0 = CAST(1 AS bit)) OR ([a].[IsDeleted] <> CAST(1 AS bit))) AND ([t].[Id] = [a].[RegionId])) AS [NoOfCenters]
FROM (
    SELECT [a0].[Id], [a0].[Name], [a0].[ProvinceId]
    FROM [AppRegions] AS [a0]
    ORDER BY (SELECT 1)
    OFFSET @__p_0 ROWS FETCH NEXT @__p_1 ROWS ONLY
) AS [t]
INNER JOIN [AppProvinces] AS [a1] ON [t].[ProvinceId] = [a1].[Id]
ORDER BY [t].[Name]
